⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Big Brother
node 1984 · 1984 · ⟦Big Brother:1984:c22eb9⟧

WHO   — Big Brother — the face of the Party
WHAT  — The object of love and fear the whole system orbits: ever-watching, never-met, the focus of the Two Minutes Hate's inverse.
WHERE — 1984 · 1984  Framework inputs: Nineteen Eighty-Four (George Orwell, 1949)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a total State needs a face to love — terror and devotion fixed on an image that may be pure fabrication.
HOW   — By omnipresent posters, the telescreen, and a cult of personality with no verifiable person behind it.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I may not exist at all — and it does not matter, because you were made to love me, and that love is the Party's whole victory.

